\mt2 This book gives the account of the Israeli people after they escaped from Egypt. We call this book
\mt1 Numbers
\c 1
\s1 The men of Israel were counted
\p 
\v 1 \w In|strong="H8141"\w* April \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w year|strong="H8141"\w* \w after|strong="H8145"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* Israeli \w people|strong="H1696"\w* \w left|strong="H3318"\w* \w Egypt|strong="H4714"\w*, \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \w spoke|strong="H1696"\w* \w to|strong="H1696"\w* \w Moses|strong="H4872"\w*/\w me|strong="H1696"\w* \w while|strong="H8141"\w* \w he|strong="H3068"\w*/\w I|strong="H4714"\w* \w was|strong="H3068"\w* \w in|strong="H8141"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* Sacred Tent, \w in|strong="H8141"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w Sinai|strong="H5514"\w* \w Desert|strong="H4057"\w*. \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \w said|strong="H1696"\w* \w to|strong="H1696"\w* \w him|strong="H3318"\w*/\w me|strong="H1696"\w*,
\v 2-3 “I want you and Aaron to determine how many Israeli men are able to fight in battles. Write down the names of all the men who are at least 20 years old, and write down the names of their clans and families.
\v 4 \add I have chosen\add* \w one|strong="H1931"\w* \w man|strong="H7218"\w* \w from|strong="H1961"\w* each \w of|strong="H1004"\w* \w the|strong="H1961"\w* \w tribes|strong="H4294"\w* \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w help|strong="H1961"\w* \w you|strong="H1004"\w* \w to|strong="H1961"\w* do \w this|strong="H1931"\w*. Each \w one|strong="H1931"\w* \w will|strong="H1961"\w* \w be|strong="H1961"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w leader|strong="H7218"\w* \w of|strong="H1004"\w* \w his|strong="H1961"\w* clan.
\p 
\v 5-15 Their names are:
\li1 Elizur, the son of Shedeur, from the tribe of Reuben;
\li1 Shelumiel, the son of Zurishaddai, from the tribe of Simeon;
\li1 Nahshon, the son of Amminadab, from the tribe of Judah;
\li1 Nethanel, the son of Zuar, from the tribe of Issachar;
\li1 Eliab, the son of Helon, from the tribe of Zebulun;
\li1 Elishama, the son of Ammihud, from the tribe of Joseph’s son Ephraim;
\li1 Gamaliel, the son of Pedahzur, from the tribe of Joseph’s son Manasseh;
\li1 Abidan, the son of Gideoni, from the tribe of Benjamin;
\li1 Ahiezer, the son of Ammishaddai, from the tribe of Dan;
\li1 Pagiel, the son of Ocran, from the tribe of Asher;
\li1 Eliasaph, the son of Deuel, from the tribe of Gad;
\li1 Ahira, the son of Enan, from the tribe of Naphtali.”
\b
\p 
\v 16 \w Those|strong="H1992"\w* \w were|strong="H3478"\w* \w the|strong="H3478"\w* \w men|strong="H7218"\w* \w whom|strong="H1992"\w* \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* chose \w from|strong="H3478"\w* \w the|strong="H3478"\w* \w people|strong="H5712"\w*. \w They|strong="H1992"\w* \w were|strong="H3478"\w* \w leaders|strong="H7218"\w* \w of|strong="H4294"\w* \w their|strong="H1992"\w* \w tribes|strong="H4294"\w*. \w They|strong="H1992"\w* \w were|strong="H3478"\w* \w the|strong="H3478"\w* \w chief|strong="H7218"\w* \w men|strong="H7218"\w* \w of|strong="H4294"\w* \w the|strong="H3478"\w* clans \w of|strong="H4294"\w* \w the|strong="H3478"\w* Israeli \w people|strong="H5712"\w*.
\p 
\v 17 Aaron \w and|strong="H4872"\w* \w Moses|strong="H4872"\w*/\w I|strong="H8034"\w* \w summoned|strong="H3947"\w* \w all|strong="H3947"\w* \w these|strong="H3947"\w* leaders,
\v 18 \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w they|strong="H5921"\w* \w gathered|strong="H6950"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w people|strong="H1121"\w* \w together|strong="H6950"\w* \w on|strong="H5921"\w* \w that|strong="H3605"\w* \w same|strong="H8034"\w* \w day|strong="H2320"\w*. \w They|strong="H5921"\w* \w listed|strong="H8034"\w*/wrote \w down|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w names|strong="H8034"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w men|strong="H1121"\w* \w who|strong="H3605"\w* \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w at|strong="H5921"\w* least 20 \w years|strong="H8141"\w* \w old|strong="H1121"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w with|strong="H1004"\w* \w their|strong="H3605"\w* \w names|strong="H8034"\w* \w they|strong="H5921"\w* wrote \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w names|strong="H8034"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w their|strong="H3605"\w* \w clans|strong="H4940"\w* \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w their|strong="H3605"\w* \w family|strong="H4940"\w* \w groups|strong="H1121"\w*
\v 19 just \w as|strong="H3068"\w* \w Moses|strong="H4872"\w*/\w I|strong="H6680"\w* \w had|strong="H3068"\w* \w commanded|strong="H6680"\w*. \w They|strong="H3068"\w* wrote \w the|strong="H3068"\w* names while ◄\w the|strong="H3068"\w* Israelis/\w we|strong="H3068"\w*► \w were|strong="H6485"\w* \w there|strong="H3068"\w* \w in|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w Sinai|strong="H5514"\w* \w Desert|strong="H4057"\w*.
\b
\p 
\v 20-43 This is \w a|strong="H3068"\w* list of the number of men who were at least 20 years old and able to fight in battles, and the names of their tribes:
\li1 There were 46,500 men from the tribe of Reuben (who was Jacob’s oldest son);
\li1 there were 59,300 men from the tribe of Simeon;
\li1 there were 45,560 men from the tribe of Gad;
\li1 there were 74,600 men from the tribe of Judah;
\li1 there were 54,400 men from the tribe of Issachar;
\li1 there were 57,400 men from the tribe of Zebulun;
\li1 there were 40,500 men from the tribe of Ephraim;
\li1 there were 32,200 men from the tribe of Manasseh;
\li1 there were 35,400 men from the tribe of Benjamin;
\li1 there were 62,700 men from the tribe of Dan;
\li1 there were 41,500 men from the tribe of Asher;
\li1 there were 53,400 men from the tribe of Naphtali.
\b
\p 
\v 44-45 That was the number of men from each tribe that Aaron and Moses/I and the twelve leaders of the tribes of Israel listed, along with the names of their clans.
\v 46 \w The|strong="H3605"\w* \w total|strong="H3605"\w* \w was|strong="H1961"\w* 603,550 \w men|strong="H3605"\w*.
\p 
\v 47 \w But|strong="H3808"\w* \w this|strong="H8432"\w* \w number|strong="H6485"\w* \w did|strong="H3808"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* include \w the|strong="H8432"\w* names \w of|strong="H4294"\w* \w the|strong="H8432"\w* \w men|strong="H6485"\w* \w of|strong="H4294"\w* \w the|strong="H8432"\w* \w tribe|strong="H4294"\w* \w of|strong="H4294"\w* \w Levi|strong="H3881"\w*,
\v 48 \w because|strong="H3068"\w* \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \w had|strong="H3068"\w* \w said|strong="H1696"\w* \w to|strong="H1696"\w* \w Moses|strong="H4872"\w*/\w me|strong="H1696"\w*,
\v 49 “\w When|strong="H1121"\w* \w you|strong="H3808"\w* ◄\w count|strong="H7218"\w*/write \w the|strong="H5375"\w* names \w of|strong="H1121"\w*► \w the|strong="H5375"\w* \w men|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H5375"\w* \w tribes|strong="H4294"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w*, do \w not|strong="H3808"\w* \w count|strong="H7218"\w* \w the|strong="H5375"\w* \w men|strong="H1121"\w* \w in|strong="H3478"\w* \w the|strong="H5375"\w* \w tribe|strong="H4294"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Levi|strong="H3881"\w*.
\v 50 \w Appoint|strong="H6485"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* male descendants \w of|strong="H3627"\w* \w Levi|strong="H3881"\w* \w to|strong="H5921"\w* \w take|strong="H5375"\w* \w care|strong="H6485"\w* \w of|strong="H3627"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* Sacred \w Tent|strong="H2583"\w* \w and|strong="H3881"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* chest inside \w it|strong="H5921"\w* \w that|strong="H3605"\w* contains \add the tablets on which are written\add* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* Ten Commandments. \w They|strong="H1992"\w* \w must|strong="H5375"\w* \w also|strong="H1992"\w* \w take|strong="H5375"\w* \w care|strong="H6485"\w* \w of|strong="H3627"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w other|strong="H3605"\w* \w things|strong="H3605"\w* \w that|strong="H3605"\w* \w are|strong="H1992"\w* inside \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w tent|strong="H2583"\w*. \add When you travel\add*, \w they|strong="H1992"\w* \w are|strong="H1992"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w ones|strong="H1992"\w* \w who|strong="H3605"\w* \w must|strong="H5375"\w* \w carry|strong="H5375"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w tent|strong="H2583"\w* \w and|strong="H3881"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w things|strong="H3605"\w* \w that|strong="H3605"\w* \w are|strong="H1992"\w* inside \w it|strong="H5921"\w*, \w and|strong="H3881"\w* \w they|strong="H1992"\w* \w must|strong="H5375"\w* \w take|strong="H5375"\w* \w care|strong="H6485"\w* \w of|strong="H3627"\w* \w it|strong="H5921"\w* \w and|strong="H3881"\w* \w set|strong="H6485"\w* \w up|strong="H5375"\w* \w their|strong="H3605"\w* \w tents|strong="H2583"\w* \w around|strong="H5439"\w* \w it|strong="H5921"\w*.
\v 51 Whenever \w it|strong="H7126"\w* \w is|strong="H4191"\w* time \w for|strong="H4191"\w* \w all|strong="H6965"\w* \w of|strong="H4191"\w* \w you|strong="H3381"\w* \w to|strong="H3381"\w* \w move|strong="H5265"\w* \add to another location\add*, \w the|strong="H7126"\w* descendants \w of|strong="H4191"\w* \w Levi|strong="H3881"\w* \w are|strong="H4908"\w* \w the|strong="H7126"\w* ones \w who|strong="H3881"\w* \w must|strong="H4191"\w* dismantle \w the|strong="H7126"\w* \w tent|strong="H2583"\w*. \w And|strong="H6965"\w* \w when|strong="H5265"\w* \w it|strong="H7126"\w* \w is|strong="H4191"\w* time \w to|strong="H3381"\w* stop \w traveling|strong="H5265"\w*, \w they|strong="H4908"\w* \w are|strong="H4908"\w* \w the|strong="H7126"\w* ones \w who|strong="H3881"\w* \w must|strong="H4191"\w* \w set|strong="H5265"\w* \w up|strong="H6965"\w* \w the|strong="H7126"\w* Sacred \w Tent|strong="H2583"\w* \w again|strong="H6965"\w*. \w Any|strong="H7126"\w* \w other|strong="H2114"\w* \w person|strong="H7126"\w* \w who|strong="H3881"\w* \w goes|strong="H3381"\w* \w near|strong="H7126"\w* \w the|strong="H7126"\w* Sacred \w Tent|strong="H2583"\w* \add to do this work\add* \w must|strong="H4191"\w* \w be|strong="H4191"\w* \w executed|strong="H4191"\w*.
\v 52 \w The|strong="H5921"\w* \w people|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* each Israeli tribe \w must|strong="H1121"\w* \w set|strong="H3478"\w* \w up|strong="H5921"\w* \w their|strong="H5921"\w* \w tents|strong="H4264"\w* \w in|strong="H5921"\w* \w their|strong="H5921"\w* own area, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w they|strong="H5921"\w* \w must|strong="H1121"\w* \w set|strong="H3478"\w* \w up|strong="H5921"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* flag/\w banner|strong="H1714"\w* \w that|strong="H3478"\w* represents \w their|strong="H5921"\w* tribe.
\v 53 \w But|strong="H3808"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w male|strong="H1121"\w* \w descendants|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Levi|strong="H3881"\w* \w must|strong="H1121"\w* \w set|strong="H3478"\w* \w up|strong="H5921"\w* \w their|strong="H5921"\w* \w tents|strong="H2583"\w* \w around|strong="H5439"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* Sacred \w Tent|strong="H2583"\w*, \w in|strong="H5921"\w* order \w to|strong="H3478"\w* \w protect|strong="H8104"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* other Israeli \w people|strong="H1121"\w* \w from|strong="H5921"\w* \w being|strong="H1961"\w* punished [MTY] \w by|strong="H5921"\w* \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \add for coming close to the Sacred Tent\add*. \w The|strong="H5921"\w* \w descendants|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Levi|strong="H3881"\w* \w are|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w ones|strong="H1121"\w* \w who|strong="H1121"\w* \w must|strong="H1121"\w* stand \w around|strong="H5439"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* Sacred \w Tent|strong="H2583"\w* \w to|strong="H3478"\w* \w guard|strong="H8104"\w* \w it|strong="H5921"\w*.”
\p 
\v 54 \w So|strong="H3651"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* Israeli \w people|strong="H1121"\w* \w did|strong="H6213"\w* \w everything|strong="H3605"\w* \w just|strong="H3605"\w* \w like|strong="H3651"\w* \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \w had|strong="H3068"\w* \w commanded|strong="H6680"\w* \w Moses|strong="H4872"\w*/\w me|strong="H6213"\w*.
\c 2
\s1 Instructions for setting up the Israeli camp
\p 
\v 1 \w Then|strong="H1696"\w* \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \w said|strong="H1696"\w* \w this|strong="H1696"\w* \w to|strong="H1696"\w* Aaron \w and|strong="H4872"\w* \w Moses|strong="H4872"\w*/\w me|strong="H1696"\w*:
\v 2 “\w When|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* Israelis \w set|strong="H3478"\w* \w up|strong="H5921"\w* \w their|strong="H5921"\w* \w tents|strong="H2583"\w*, \w they|strong="H5921"\w* \w should|strong="H3478"\w* \w set|strong="H3478"\w* \w them|strong="H5921"\w* \w up|strong="H5921"\w* \w in|strong="H5921"\w* areas \w that|strong="H3478"\w* \w surround|strong="H5439"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* Sacred \w Tent|strong="H2583"\w*, \w but|strong="H5921"\w* \w not|strong="H1121"\w* close \w to|strong="H3478"\w* \w it|strong="H5921"\w*. \w The|strong="H5921"\w* \w people|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w each|strong="H5439"\w* tribe \w must|strong="H1121"\w* \w set|strong="H3478"\w* \w up|strong="H5921"\w* \w their|strong="H5921"\w* \w tents|strong="H2583"\w* \w in|strong="H5921"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* different \w area|strong="H5439"\w*. \w Each|strong="H5439"\w* tribe \w must|strong="H1121"\w* erect \w in|strong="H5921"\w* \w that|strong="H3478"\w* \w area|strong="H5439"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w banner|strong="H1714"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w their|strong="H5921"\w* own clan \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* flag \w that|strong="H3478"\w* represents \w their|strong="H5921"\w* tribe.
\b
\p 
\v 3-4 The people of the tribes of Judah, Issachar, and Zebulun must set up their tents on the east side of the Sacred Tent, close to their tribal flags. These are the names of the leaders of those tribes and the number of soldiers whom they will lead:
\pi1 Nahshon, the son of Amminadab, will be the leader of the 74,600 men of the tribe of Judah.
\pi1 
\v 5-6 Nethanel, the son of Zuar, will be the leader of the 54,500 men of the tribe of Issachar.
\pi1 
\v 7-8 Eliab, the son of Helon, will be the leader of the 57,400 men of the tribe of Zebulun.
\pi1 
\v 9 \w So|strong="H6485"\w* \w there|strong="H3605"\w* \w will|strong="H3063"\w* \w be|strong="H3063"\w* 86,400 \w troops|strong="H6635"\w* \w on|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* east side \add of the Sacred Tent\add*. \w Whenever|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* Israelis \w move|strong="H5265"\w* \w to|strong="H3063"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* new location, \w those|strong="H3605"\w* three tribes \w must|strong="H4264"\w* \w go|strong="H5265"\w* \w in|strong="H6635"\w* \w front|strong="H7223"\w* \w of|strong="H6635"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* others.
\b
\pi1 
\v 10-11 The tribes of Reuben, Simeon, and Gad must set up their tents on the south side of the Sacred Tent, close to their tribal flags. These are the names of the leaders of those tribes and the number of men whom they will lead:
\pi1 Elizur, the son of Shedeur, will be the leader of the 46,500 men of the tribe of Reuben.
\pi1 
\v 12-13 Shelumiel, the son of Zurishaddai, will be the leader of the 59,300 men of the tribe of Simeon.
\pi1 
\v 14-15 Eliasaph, the son of Deuel, will be the leader of the 45,650 men of the tribe of Gad.
\pi1 
\v 16 \w So|strong="H6485"\w* \w there|strong="H3605"\w* \w will|strong="H6635"\w* \w be|strong="H4264"\w* 151,450 \w troops|strong="H6635"\w* \w on|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* south side \w of|strong="H6635"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* Sacred Tent. \w Those|strong="H3605"\w* three tribes \w will|strong="H6635"\w* follow \w the|strong="H3605"\w* first group \add when the Israelis travel\add*.
\b
\pi1 
\v 17 \w Behind|strong="H5921"\w* \w that|strong="H3651"\w* group \w will|strong="H3027"\w* walk \w the|strong="H5921"\w* descendants \w of|strong="H3027"\w* \w Levi|strong="H3881"\w*, \w who|strong="H3881"\w* \w will|strong="H3027"\w* carry \w the|strong="H5921"\w* Sacred \w Tent|strong="H2583"\w*. \w The|strong="H5921"\w* Israelis \w will|strong="H3027"\w* march \w in|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w same|strong="H3651"\w* \w order|strong="H3027"\w* \w that|strong="H3651"\w* \w they|strong="H3651"\w* always \w set|strong="H5265"\w* \w up|strong="H5921"\w* \w their|strong="H5921"\w* \w tents|strong="H4264"\w*. Each tribe \w will|strong="H3027"\w* carry \w its|strong="H5921"\w* \w own|strong="H3027"\w* flag.
\b
\pi1 
\v 18-19 The tribes of Ephraim, Manasseh, and Benjamin must set up their tents on the west side of the Sacred Tent, close to their tribal flags. These are the names of the leaders of those tribes and number of men whom they will lead:
\pi1 Elishama, the son of Ammihud, will be the leader of the 40,500 men of the tribe of Ephraim.
\pi1 
\v 20-21 Gamaliel, the son of Pedahzur, will be the leader of the 32,200 men of the tribe of Manasseh.
\pi1 
\v 22-23 Abidan, the son of Gideoni, will be the leader of the 35,400 men of the tribe of Benjamin.
\pi1 
\v 24 \w So|strong="H6485"\w* \w there|strong="H3605"\w* \w will|strong="H6635"\w* \w be|strong="H4264"\w* 108,100 \w troops|strong="H6635"\w* \w on|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* west side \w of|strong="H6635"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* Sacred Tent. \w Those|strong="H3605"\w* \w three|strong="H7992"\w* tribes \w will|strong="H6635"\w* follow \w the|strong="H3605"\w* second group, \add behind the descendants of Levi\add*.
\b
\pi1 
\v 25-26 The tribes of Dan, Asher, and Naphtali must set up their tents on the north side of the Sacred Tent, close to their tribal flags. These are the names of the leaders of those tribes and the number of men whom they will lead:
\pi1 Ahiezer, the son of Ammishaddai, will be the leader of the 62,700 men of the tribe of Dan.
\pi1 
\v 27-28 Pagiel, the son of Ocran, will be the leader of the 41,500 men of the tribe of Asher.
\pi1 
\v 29-30 Ahira, the son of Enan, will be the leader of the 53,400 men of the tribe of Naphtali.
\pi1 
\v 31 \w So|strong="H6485"\w* \w there|strong="H3605"\w* \w will|strong="H3605"\w* \w be|strong="H4264"\w* 157,600 \w troops|strong="H4264"\w* \w on|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* north side \w of|strong="H4264"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* Sacred Tent. \w Those|strong="H3605"\w* three tribes \w will|strong="H3605"\w* \w be|strong="H4264"\w* last. \w They|strong="H3605"\w* \w must|strong="H4264"\w* carry \w their|strong="H3605"\w* own flags \w when|strong="H6485"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* Israelis travel.”
\b
