\v 35 \w From|strong="H5265"\w* \w there|strong="H1961"\w*, \w the|strong="H1961"\w* Israelis \w continued|strong="H1961"\w* walking \add east\add* until \w they|strong="H5971"\w* arrived \w at|strong="H1961"\w* \w Hazeroth|strong="H2698"\w* \add town\add*, where \w they|strong="H5971"\w* stopped \w and|strong="H5971"\w* stayed \add for a long time\add*.
\c 12
\s1 Miriam and Aaron were jealous of Moses
\p 
\v 1-2 \add Moses’/My older sister\add* Miriam and \add his/my older brother\add* Aaron were saying this: “Is Moses the only one to whom \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* has spoken messages to tell to us [RHQ]? Does \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* not speak messages to us two also?” \add They told people that\add* they were saying that because Moses/I had married \w a|strong="H3068"\w* woman who was \w a|strong="H3068"\w* descendant of the Cush people-group, \add but they were really saying that because they ◄were jealous/did not want Moses/me to be the only leader of the Israeli people►\add*. But \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* heard what they were saying.
\p 
\v 3 \add The truth was that\add* \w Moses|strong="H4872"\w*/\w I|strong="H5921"\w* \w was|strong="H4872"\w* \w very|strong="H3966"\w* \w humble|strong="H6035"\w*. \w He|strong="H3605"\w*/\w I|strong="H5921"\w* \w was|strong="H4872"\w* \w more|strong="H3966"\w* \w humble|strong="H6035"\w* \w than|strong="H5921"\w* \w anyone|strong="H3605"\w* \w else|strong="H3605"\w* \w on|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* earth \add and Moses/I had not appointed himself/myself to be their leader\add*.
\p 
\v 4 \w So|strong="H3318"\w* \w immediately|strong="H6597"\w* \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* spoke \w to|strong="H3318"\w* \w Moses|strong="H4872"\w*/\w me|strong="H3318"\w* \w and|strong="H4872"\w* \w to|strong="H3318"\w* Aaron \w and|strong="H4872"\w* \w Miriam|strong="H4813"\w*. \w He|strong="H3068"\w* \w said|strong="H3318"\w*, “\w All|strong="H3068"\w* \w three|strong="H7969"\w* \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w you|strong="H3318"\w* must \w go|strong="H3318"\w* \w and|strong="H4872"\w* stand \w at|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* Sacred Tent.” \w So|strong="H3318"\w* \w they|strong="H3068"\w*/\w we|strong="H3068"\w* \w did|strong="H3068"\w* \w that|strong="H3068"\w*.
\v 5 \w Then|strong="H3318"\w* \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \w descended|strong="H3381"\w* \w to|strong="H3381"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w entrance|strong="H6607"\w* \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* tent \w in|strong="H3068"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w cloud|strong="H6051"\w* \add that resembled a huge white\add* \w pillar|strong="H5982"\w*. \w He|strong="H3068"\w* told Aaron \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w Miriam|strong="H4813"\w* \w to|strong="H3381"\w* step \w forward|strong="H3318"\w*, \w so|strong="H7121"\w* \w they|strong="H3068"\w* \w did|strong="H3068"\w*.
